    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-05-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-05-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="133"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d133">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/462.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador to Great
                            Britain</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-05-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 31, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>If a list can be given of proposed industrial enterprises in Manchuria, and these
                    do not at all relate to railroads, Sir Edward Grey is confident there will be no
                    further objection from either Japan or Russia. Neither objects to the currency
                    reform portion of the loan.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reid</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
